# Clear Visual Hierarchy

The most important element on a screen must draw the eye first. Hierarchy is intentional, never accidental.

## 1. Typography scales

Use only **3–4 font sizes** per screen. Distinguish levels with weight and color, not size alone.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — five sizes, hierarchy only by px
<p className="text-3xl">Title</p>
<p className="text-2xl">Subtitle</p>
<p className="text-xl">Section</p>
<p className="text-lg">Body</p>
<p className="text-sm">Note</p>

// ✅ GOOD — three sizes; weight carries rank
<h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground">Title</h1>
<p className="text-base font-normal text-foreground">Body copy…</p>
<span className="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">Meta</span>
```

## 2. Primary actions

Exactly **one** prominent primary button per screen (or per focused modal). Secondary actions use outline, phantom, or ghost styles.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — two solid CTAs compete
<button className="bg-brand text-white">Save</button>
<button className="bg-brand text-white">Cancel</button>

// ✅ GOOD — one solid primary; secondary is quiet
<button className="bg-brand text-white">Save</button>
<button className="border border-border bg-transparent">Cancel</button>
```

## 3. Proximity

Related elements sit closer together than unrelated ones. Whitespace encodes grouping.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — equal gap everywhere; no groups
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
  <label>Email</label>
  <input />
  <label>Password</label>  {/* looks as far from Email as from Submit */}
  <button>Submit</button>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — tight within fields; larger gap between groups
<div className="flex flex-col gap-6">
  <div className="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
    <label>Email</label>
    <input />
  </div>
  <div className="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
    <label>Password</label>
    <input />
  </div>
  <button>Submit</button>
</div>
```

## 4. Readability

- Cap body line length at **60–75 characters** (`max-w-prose` / `max-w-2xl`).
- Body text: minimum **150% line height** (`leading-relaxed` or `leading-[1.5]`).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="max-w-full leading-none">Long unbroken paragraph…</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<p className="max-w-prose text-base leading-relaxed">Long paragraph…</p>
```

## 5. Contrast

Important text must meet a high contrast ratio against its background. Dim non-essential metadata.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — primary copy muted; meta as loud as the title
<h1 className="text-muted-foreground">Report title</h1>
<span className="text-foreground">Updated 2h ago</span>

// ✅ GOOD — content loud; meta quiet
<h1 className="text-foreground font-semibold">Report title</h1>
<span className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Updated 2h ago</span>
```

## Checklist before shipping UI

- [ ] Eye lands on the primary message or action within 1 second
- [ ] ≤4 type sizes; weight/color reinforce rank
- [ ] One solid primary CTA; others are secondary styles
- [ ] Related items cluster; unrelated groups have more space
- [ ] Body ≤75ch, ≥1.5 line-height; meta is visually quieter
